predictions. There are few attempts of post-hoc explainers [14, 22,
45, 48] to provide explanations for trained GNNs; while the work
on self-explainable GNNs is rather limited.
We aim to develop self-explainable GNNs. In particular, for each
unlabeled node ğ‘£ğ‘– , we want to find ğ¾ most similar labeled nodes with ğ‘£ğ‘– , and simultaneously utilize these similar nodes to predict ğ‘£ğ‘– â€™s label and provide explanation of the prediction. Since both node features and local structure are important for classificaiton,
the similarity should be measured in terms of both node features and the n-hop subgraph centered at each node. Sample explanations can be: (i) â€œnode ğ‘£ğ‘– is classified as class ğµ because these ğ¾ nodes have the most similar node features and n-hop subgrph with that of ğ‘£ğ‘– , and most of these ğ¾ nodes belong to class ğµâ€; (ii) â€œnode ğ‘£ğ‘– is similar to node ğ‘£ ğ‘— because the n-hop subgraphs centered at these two nodes are similar. For example, this part of the structure and
attributes of ğ‘£ğ‘– â€™s n-hop subgraph matches to that of ğ‘£ ğ‘— â€™sâ€. Let Gğ‘ (ğ‘›) (ğ‘£ğ‘– ) = (ğ‘£ğ‘– âˆª N (ğ‘›) (ğ‘£ğ‘– ), Eğ‘ (ğ‘›) (ğ‘£ğ‘– )) be the n-hop subgraph
