4.2 Self-Explainable Classification

With the similarity metric described in Section 4.1, we are able to identify the interpretable ğ¾-nearest labeled nodes to predict and explain the label of the target node. Next, we introduce the details of the prediction process, discussions about the explanations, and the loss function that ensures classification accuracy.

